  <description type="morphology">Plants erect, usually appearing small and tufted, 1.8–4.5(–6.5) cm. Basal leaves: blade ovate to ovate-orbiculate, 0.5–1.7 × 0.4–1.4 cm, base subcordate, truncate, or attenuate, apex usually obtuse, surfaces usually glabrous. Cauline leaves: petiole 0.5–3.8 cm; blade 0.6–1.5 × 0.4–1.4 cm. Peduncles 1.7–5 cm, bracteoles usually opposite. Flowers: sepal margins usually eciliate; lowest petal 7–13(–14) mm; style head sparsely bearded. Seeds 1.5 mm. 2n = 20.</description>
